it Capability\"},{\"category\":\"Coda\",\"value\":0,\"group\":\"Edit Capability\"},{\"category\":\"GitBook\",\"value\":80,\"group\":\"Edit Capability\"},{\"category\":\"Confluence\",\"value\":95,\"group\":\"Knowledge Base\"},{\"category\":\"GitHub Pages\",\"value\":70,\"group\":\"Knowledge Base\"},{\"category\":\"Notion\",\"value\":90,\"group\":\"Knowledge Base\"},{\"category\":\"Coda\",\"value\":90,\"group\":\"Knowledge Base\"},{\"category\":\"GitBook\",\"value\":95,\"group\":\"Knowledge Base\"}],\"width\":800,\"axisXTitle\":\"Platforms\",\"title\":\"REAL HTML Import & Interactive Rendering Capabilities\",\"group\":true,\"height\":500} View 🎯 CORRECTED ANALYSIS: Platforms That ACTUALLY Import Interactive HTML Pages You were absolutely right to question Coda! Based on my research, Coda explicitly does NOT support HTML import/rendering for security reasons. Here are the platforms that genuinely can import and render your GenSpark HTML pages: Top Recommendation: Atlassian Confluence Why Confluence is Perfect for Your HTML Import Needs: Feature\tImplementation Steps\tExpected Input\tExpected Output\tBusiness Impact HTML File Import\tSpace Settings → Import → Select HTML files\tGenSpark .html files, entire folders\tNative Confluence pages with preserved formatting\tDirect content migration HTML Macro Support\tInsert → Other macros → HTML macro\tRaw HTML code, embedded content\tFully rendered interactive elements\tMaintain GenSpark interactivity Table Creation\tNative table editor with advanced features\tData, formulas, formatting\tProfessional database-style tables\tSuperior client deliverables Search & Organization\tBuilt-in enterprise search across all content\tKeywords, tags, content types\tInstant searchable knowledge base\tRapid content retrieval Step-by-Step Confluence Setup for HTML Import: Phase 1: Setup & Import (Week 1) Create Confluence Space - Set up dedicated space for GenSpark content Bulk HTML Import - Use Space Settings → Import to upload entire GenSpark archive Verify Rendering - Check that interactive elements display correctly Organize Structure - Create page hierarchy matching your content strategy Phase 2: Enhancement & Tables (Week 2) Advanced Tables - Convert static data into dynamic, sortable tables Macros Integration - Add interactive elements (charts, forms, calculators) Template Creation - Build reusable page templates for consistent formatting Search Optimization - Configure labels and metadata for findability Alternative Option 1: GitHub Pages + Repository GitHub Pages Implementation Guide: Implementation Area\tTactical Steps\tTime Investment\tRevenue Opportunity Repository Setup\tCreate organization repo, upload HTML files\t2-3 hours\tProfessional client portfolios GitHub Pages Activation\tSettings → Pages → Deploy from main branch\t30 minutes\tLive, searchable knowledge base Custom Domain\tConfigure your domain for branded access\t1 hour\tWhite-label client deliverables Editing Workflow\tUse GitHub's web editor or connect VS Code\t1-2 hours\tDirect HTML editing capabilities Advantages: ✅ 100% HTML compatibility - Renders exactly like GenSpark ✅ Version control - Track all changes and iterations ✅ Free hosting - No monthly costs ✅ Direct editing - Modify HTML/CSS/JS directly in browser ✅ Search functionality - Add search with Jekyll or custom solutions Alternative Option 2: GitBook (User-Friendly Choice) GitBook Implementation Strategy: Setup Process: Create GitBook Space - Sign up at GitBook.com Import Content - Use GitBook's HTML import feature Customize Design - Apply your branding and themes Configure Search - Enable full-text search across all content Key Benefits: ✅ Notion-like interface but with HTML import support ✅ Excellent table editor - Advanced table creation tools ✅ Markdown + HTML - Best of both worlds ✅ Team collaboration - Multiple editors with permissions ✅ Public/Private spaces - Control access levels Tactical Implementation Flowchart Using Tool | MCP Chart Server MCP: generate_flow